# Beartropy Charts - Cursor Rules

## Project Context
This project uses **Beartropy Charts**, SVG-based chart components for the TALL stack (Tailwind, Alpine, Laravel, Livewire).

## Chart Components

### Available Tags
```blade
<x-bt-bar-chart :data="$data" />
<x-bt-line-chart :data="$data" />
<x-bt-pie-chart :data="$data" />
<x-bt-donut-chart :data="$data" />
<x-bt-radar-chart :data="$data" />
<x-bt-polar-chart :data="$data" />
<x-bt-chart-wrapper title="Title">...</x-bt-chart-wrapper>
```

### Data Formats
```php
# Simple (bar, pie, donut, polar)
['Jan' => 100, 'Feb' => 200]

# With colors
[['label' => 'A', 'value' => 100, 'color' => '#3B82F6']]

# Multi-dataset (line, radar)
[['label' => 'Series', 'data' => ['Jan' => 500], 'color' => '#hex']]

# Radar axes
[['label' => 'Product', 'Speed' => 80, 'Power' => 90]]
```

### Common Props
- `:data` (array) — Chart data
- `height` (string) — Tailwind height classes, default "h-48 md:h-64"
- `title` (string) — Chart title
- `:border` (bool) — Show border, default true
- `formatValues` (string) — printf format, e.g. "$%s"
- `chartColor` (string) — Color palette override
- `legendPosition` (string) — "right", "bottom", "none", "hidden"

### Best Practices
- Always pass data as bound prop: `:data="$data"` not `data="..."`
- Use `formatValues` for currency/percentage: `formatValues="$%s"` or `formatValues="%s%%"`
- Wrap with `<x-bt-chart-wrapper>` and set `:border="false"` on inner chart to avoid double borders
- Charts are Livewire-compatible — use computed properties for reactive data
